'''Kaka Shrine''' (かかじんじゃ) is a shrine in {{ill|lt=Shimane-chō|Q7496828|qid=Q7496828|1=Shimane, Shimane}}, {{ill|lt=Matsue|Q207321|qid=Q207321|1=Matsue}}, {{ill|lt=Shimane Prefecture|Q132751|qid=Q132751|1=Shimane Prefecture}}. It is also called Kuredo Daimyōjin.

=== Enshrined deities ===
Its principal deity is {{ill|lt=Kisagaihime and Umugihime|Q11296639|qid=Q11296639|lt=Kisakabihime-no-Mikoto|1=Kisagaihime and Umugihime}}<ref>{{Cite web|和書|title=松江 加賀神社（かかじんじゃ）|url=http://hakuto.tea-nifty.com/blog/2019/02/post-5677.html|website=鳥取市 白兎観光協会スタッフブログ|accessdate=2022-01-09}}</ref>, with associated deities {{ill|lt=Izanagi|Q813858|qid=Q813858|lt=Izanagi-no-Mikoto|1=Izanagi}}, {{ill|lt=Izanami|Q682306|qid=Q682306|lt=Izanami-no-Mikoto|1=Izanami}}, {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|qid=Q455602|1=Amaterasu}}, and {{ill|lt=Sarutahiko|Q3090037|qid=Q3090037|lt=Sarutahiko-no-Mikoto|1=Sarutahiko Ōkami}}.

=== History ===
The ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'' includes an entry for "Kaka Shrine." It was originally enshrined in {{ill|lt=Kaka no Kukedo|Q11399639|qid=Q11399639|1=Kaka no kukedo}}, and later moved to its present site. In ''Izumo Fudoki-shō'' it is called "Kukedo Daimyōjin," while in ''Unyōshi'' it is called "Kuredo Daimyōjin," with Izanagi-no-Mikoto and Izanami-no-Mikoto as enshrined deities.

=== Precinct shrines ===
* Higashisue Shrine
* Hinomisaki Shrine
* Nishisue Shrine
* Ebisu Shrine
* Kumano Shrine

=== Festivals ===
The Shanin Festival is held on October 21, and the Otokunichi Festival on October 29<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|和書|title=島根県立古代出雲歴史博物館｜松江市の祭リスト|url=http://www.izm.ed.jp/cms/kodai/matsuri_matsue.html|website=www.izm.ed.jp|accessdate=2022-01-09}}</ref>. Like {{ill|lt=Ise Jingū|Q687168|qid=Q687168|1=Ise Grand Shrine}}, a shikinen {{ill|lt=sengū|Q2271023|qid=Q2271023|1=Sengū}} is conducted every 20 years, and a boat-pulling ritual is held during the main transfer festival<ref name=":0" />.

